{
  "texts": [
    "The former is mostly related to updates regarding the situation, asking for help, and supporting the people of Ukraine, the latter covers a more political side of the overall conflict.",
    "Both topics are in total more discussed by those RU users that switch language (+62.5%, χ 2 (1) = 22.061, p < 0.001; +100%, χ 2 (1) = 7.312, p = 0.007).",
    "However, once we control for their total amount of tweets in our dataset, i.e.",
    "we compute a relative share of war related tweets for each user, the differences shrink and turn non-significant (+4.71%, χ 2 (1) = 0.063, p = 0.801; +17.6%, χ 2 (1) = 0.543, p = 0.461).",
    "In our work, we collected geo-tagged tweets from Ukraine and analyzed tweeting activity and language choice before and during the Russian war in Ukraine from 9th January 2020 to 12th October 2022."
  ]
}